---
title: Sesame Beef Tacos with Quick-Pickled Veggies and Chili Sour Cream
description: Instead of going the traditional route with these tacos, we decided to mix things up with a Korean-style sesame beef filling. The filling gets a kick from *gochugaru*—chili flakes traditionally used in dishes like kimchi and bulgogi. It’s an unconventional choice, perhaps, but one that lives up to the maxim that everything tastes better in a tortilla.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5d9dec4d4ba8497a8c3620d7-a69b0374.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sesame-beef-tacos-5d9dec4d4ba8497a8c3620d7-8eb28704.pdf
cuisine: Korean
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sesame-beef-tacos-5d9dec4d4ba8497a8c3620d7
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 810 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1480 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @radishes{3} and @Persian cucumber{1} into
rounds. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}. Pick @cilantro{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; discard
stems.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine radishes, cucumber, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, 1 tsp
@sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Taste and add a
pinch more sugar if you like a sweeter pickle. Set aside, stirring occasionally,
until ready to serve.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp} and a pinch of @gochugaru (Korean chili flakes){1%tsp}
(taste and add more from there if desired; save a little for steps 4 and 6). Season with
salt and pepper.

> Gochugaru are chili flakes traditionally used in dishes like kimchi and bulgogi.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallions
and @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Add @ground beef{10%oz}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and 1 tsp
@sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings). Cook, breaking up meat into pieces,
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in @sesame oil{1%tbsp}, half the
@soy sauce{2%tbsp} (use all for 4), half the @sriracha{2%tsp}, and a pinch of chili flakes to taste. Taste
and season with salt, pepper, and up to ½ tsp more @sugar{1/2%tsp}.

While filling cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Spread a bit of chili sour cream onto each tortilla, then top with filling, a bit of pickled
veggies, cilantro, and as much remaining sriracha and chili flakes as you like. Serve with any
remaining pickled veggies on the side.